A Mafdet Ledger House commission has identified forged cairn tablets circulating in the Measure's Rest archive that misrepresent historical toll precedents in ways that benefit current Red Sand Accounts territorial claims. The Kowloon scholar embedded at the archive requires a physical specimen for authentication analysis before the commission can challenge the precedents on legal grounds. Recover one forged tablet for examination.
The forged cairn tablet has been delivered to the Kowloon scholar for analysis. The examination confirmed that the forgery was executed with Synod ritual inscription tools, providing a direct evidentiary link between the Synod network and the Red Sand Accounts territory disputes. The authentication report has been transmitted to the Mafdet Ledger House commission and forwarded to the Kowloon Jade Clerk review board.

